==English==

===Etymology===
From Late Latin ''[[auriphrigiatus]]''; {{L.}} ''[[aurum]]'' "gold" + Late Latin ''[[phrygiare]]'' "to adorn with Phrygian needlework", or "with embroidery"; perhaps corrupted from some other word.

===Adjective===
'''auriphrygiate'''
# Embroidered or decorated with [[gold]].

